Conditus: some texts have positus. Note the play on the word Gonditor; the infinite Conditor of the preceding stanza is here conditus, hidden, sheltered. Fascia may be either the subject of oinyz‘t, or the ablative. In the latter ease Viryo-Mater is the subj. of cinyz’ae viz„ the Virgin- Mother‚ with a tight band, binds the hands and feet of God. The former is preferable.
